It is too cold and icy for walking and my friends are afraid that I could hurt my leg. But I did get to romp for a couple of minutes before I started to act too much like Confetti. I LOVE the snow!

So my friend took me for a ride in his mobile play room. I got to hang out, and relax, and bark at stuff as it passed by.
And I got good news about my leg. The vet said the x-ray showed it is healing nicely. I donâ€™t even have to go back! And I can return to normal activity??! My friends had to ask what that meant. Three 30-minute walks a day was the answer. Well LOL, that isnâ€™t normal Confetti activity. Itâ€™s still going to be some months until Confetti can be Confetti again...#ttarecovery #adoptme #adoptlove #boxerpitmix #adoptconfettialready #shelterdogneedsagoodhome #rbarishelter

I did not let my Daisy do jumping up or off of anything more than a foot high for close to six months. But climbed many hills and trails building the muscles. We went trudging through snow on leash too at 4 months post op. Just know where your icy spots are. Off leash she would be bounding like a gazelle! Now she's bounding up my retaining wall chasing her brother. She is now 15 months post TTA. Be patient, It is coming...
@barbarabrossok Thanks! The vet said, NO jumping! ...and my friends said NO jumping until late April...but as soon as it warms up, Iâ€™m hitting the trails...

AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION!!! Meet Bradford a super handsome Hound/Shepherd mix born around 2009. Bradford was recently abandoned at a local shelter alone and afraid. He is now safe and warm in his foster home and adjusting well. Bradford is a calm, well-mannered and very attentive boy. He absolutely loves everyone he meets!!! He is house trained and rides great in the car. He is great with other dogs. He enjoys napping in the sun and chasing squirrels in the yard.
He knows basic commands such as come, sit and lie down. He is current on vaccines, neutered and microchipped. He currently weighs 64lbs and is full grown. Bradford will make a very loyal companion, and is now looking for a forever home. Please contact us today at adopt@carolinapaws.com to meet

Meet shy boy Gunner. #A5139347 Gunner is 3 year old pitbull. What he lacks in confidence he makes up for in sweetness. Gunner needs an adopter who will be patient with him and show him he is safe. We donâ€™t know what kind of adventures he had but we are sure it was super scary out there by himself. He is very shy at first but when he gets to know you he comes out of his shell and his tail will start to wag. Gunner knows his basic commands and is great on a leash. Gunner also lights up when he sees other dogs, so we believe he would be a good addition in a home with other pets. Gunner is a very sweet boy who just needs a little time and love invested into him.
Available for adoption at the Castaic Shelter. 31044 N. Charlie Canyon Rd. Castaic, Ca. 91384. 661-257-3191 Hours: Mon-Thurs 12-7 and Fri-Sun 10-5. Closed Holidays.
